            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Move</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Dong Hoi City is about 500 km from Hanoi, about 1,000 km from Ho Chi Minh City. Means of transportation to Dong Hoi City are quite diverse and convenient for tourists.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">From Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City, there are direct flights to Dong Hoi with round-trip ticket prices from 2 to 3 million VND. The frequency of flights to Quang Binh is not much, usually only 2 flights per day. Flight time Hanoi - Dong Hoi is nearly 1 hour, Ho Chi Minh City - Dong Hoi is nearly 2 hours.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Dong Hoi Station is a stop for all Thong Nhat trains, SE trains or QB trains. One-way train ticket prices range from 450,000 to 1.4 million VND per person depending on class and seat or bed.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Many bus companies have the Quang Binh route, running night or day. The route Hanoi - Dong Hoi City has Hung Long, Hoang Linh, Phuong Trang, Doi Hien ticket price each way is 300,000-500,000 VND per person. Travel time is about 8-9 hours. From Ho Chi Minh City, there are Hoang Long, A Ba, Loc Thuy bus companies with ticket prices 400,000-800,000 VND per person each way. Time about 20 hours.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">With personal cars, tourists follow National Highway 1A or Ho Chi Minh Road. Many sections now have expressways, shortening travel time. From Hanoi to Dong Hoi, it takes about 10 hours if there is no traffic jam and short rest time. Note that on the first and last days of holidays, roads are often congested for long periods, especially at the gateway to Hanoi.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">If you want to see the scenery, you can travel along Ho Chi Minh Road. The shortest section connecting National Highway 1A and Ho Chi Minh Road is in Quang Binh. Note that phone signal may be lost in some places on this road and drivers need to comply with speed regulations and pay attention when passing through residential areas. Travel time is 2-3 hours longer than National Highway 1A, without toll stations. The Ho Chi Minh Trail takes tourists along the Truong Son range, through famous national parks such as Phong Nha - Ke Bang and Cuc Phuong forest.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">In Quang Binh province, rent a taxi or rent a car at Le Loi, Tran Hung Dao, Huu Nghi streets... in Dong Hoi City. Motorbikes can be rented at hotels, 100,000 - 150,000 VND per day.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Accommodation</pclass="handbook-title-1>
            <p>Accommodation services in Quang Binh are developed and have many options from hotels, motels to homestays, farmstays or camping.</p>
            <p>In Dong Hoi, you can choose to stay in the city center area such as Ly Thuong Kiet and Tran Hung Dao streets or hotels with beautiful locations near Nhat Le beach on Truong Phap street. 4-5 star hotels in the city include Meliá Vinpearl Quang Binh, Muong Thanh Holiday, Muong Thanh Luxury Nhat Le, Sun Spa Resort, Celina Peninsula Resort, Gold Coast, Saigon Quang Binh... with prices from 600,000 VND to 2 million VND per night.</p>
            <p>Specifically, in the Phong Nha - Ke Bang national park area (Bo Trach district), tourists should choose resorts close to nature such as Chay Lap Farmstay, Nguyen Shack - Phong Nha Eco, Phong Nha Coco Riverside, Phong Nha Nha Lake House, Lucky Home... Each night here costs from 400,000 to 2 million VND per room for two people.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Sights and entertainment</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Phong Nha - Ke Bang National Park</b>: Phong Nha - Ke Bang National Park is recognized by UNESCO as a World Natural Heritage. This place has more than 400 caves with a total length of 220 km, three main rivers are Chay River, Son River and Trooc River. The national park is located in Bo Trach and Minh Hoa districts, about 50 km from Dong Hoi city.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Ngang Pass</b>: As the natural boundary between Ha Tinh and Quang Binh provinces, Ngang Pass crosses the Hoanh Son range, and is a critical checkpoint on National Highway 1A. The pass is famous in the poem Crossing Deo Ngang by Ba Huyen Thanh Quan. The pass is 6 km long, the peak is about 250 m high. At the top of the pass, there is still "Heaven's Gate" - a relic of the Hoanh Son Quan pass built in 1833. Since 2004, the Deo Ngang road tunnel has been built, replacing the mountain pass section.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Vung Chua - Yen Island</b>: This is a scenic spot in Tho Son village, Quang Dong commune, Quang Trach district, right at the foot of Ngang pass, about 4 km south, more than 2 km east of National Highway 1A. Vung Chua is a peaceful beach, outside the sea there is Yen Island, considered a screen creating a charming scene. Dragon Mountain in this area is the resting place of General Vo Nguyen Giap. Here, every day thousands of people from all over come to offer incense, especially during the holidays. However, this area will occasionally be closed, visitors need to contact in advance for information.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Chay River - Dark Cave</b>: Chay River originates from the limestone massif and flows through the villages, combined with Dark Cave, a cave with an ancient stalactite system that represents the geological tectonic process of the Phong Nha - Ke area. Bang creates a tourist route to explore nature. Currently, Chay River - Dark Cave is being exploited in the form of exploration with many services such as zipline river bathing, zipline exploring caves, kayaking to explore Chay River, swimming through Thuy Tien Lake in Dark Cave and young mud bathing. good for health...</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Mooc spring</b>: Mooc spring tourist area is located in Bo Trach district, about 70 km from Dong Hoi city, on the west branch of Ho Chi Minh road. The stream is located right in the middle of the valley, surrounded by limestone mountains, along the banks of the Chay River. The stream here is green all year round, on sunny summer days, the water is even greener. There are many fun and exploratory activities here such as swimming races, kayaking, fishing, and ziplining. Visitors must purchase admission tickets and tickets for each game.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>All-terrain vehicle through the forest (ATV)</b>: Tour "Exploring the ironwood forest - Kong's house" by 4-wheeled all-terrain vehicle (ATV) operates in Tan Hoa commune, Minh Hoa district. This is where director Jordan Vogt-Roberts chose as the setting for the Hollywood blockbuster "Kong: Skull Island" in 2016. ATVs are multi-functional off-road vehicles that can move on many types of mountain passes and terrain. forests, sand dunes or many obstacles. During the 2-hour tour, visitors control the road themselves, drive through the forest, and conquer every bend, slope, cross streams and run in dark tunnels.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Cuisine</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Banh loc cake</b>: a delicious dish not to be missed when visiting Dong Hoi. The cake has a crust made from tapioca starch, is filled with shrimp, fatty meat, and wrapped in banana leaves. When steamed, the crust is transparent and has a rich flavor. Banh loc cake in Quang Binh also has green bean filling.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Tapioca bread</b>: is a breakfast gift that combines hot bread sandwiched with about 7-8 tapioca cakes, topped with sauce and green onions. The dish is sold in Dong Hoi market or roadside stalls for about 10,000-15,000 VND each.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Porridge soup</b>: has a strong sweet broth flavor, soft rice noodles, and a little spicy chopped green vegetables. Besides Dong Hoi City, some other places that have this dish are Ba Don town. Ba Don porridge soup is rich in the flavor of sea fish such as scad, herring, pomfret... served with golden ramen.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Thac Lac fish ball noodle soup</b>: has broth cooked from fish bones or pork bones, served with pickled purple onions and sliced ​​chili. Raw vegetables served with lettuce and banana flowers. Each bowl is sold for about 30,000 VND, suitable for breakfast.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Great-great-grandson</b>: is a dish of people along the Gianh River. In the same family as mussels, great-grandsons are only the size of green beans. Quang Binh people create all kinds of dishes from stir-fried stone cakes with fried great-grandchildren, to vermicelli, porridge, soup or stir-fried young jackfruit.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Oyster porridge</b>: is a dish invited to guests by people in Quan Hau town, Quang Ninh district right at the gateway of Dong Hoi city. Nhat Le river oysters are fresh and fatty, creating a bowl of rustic porridge, sweet and fragrant, with an unforgettable flavor.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Banh hoi</b>: is a dish not to be missed when coming to Quang Binh. The cake is similar to banh xeo, but thicker, filled with beef and fresh shrimp. Diners will use rice paper to roll a piece of banh hoi, with vegetables dipped in sweet and sour fish sauce.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Seafood</b>: in Quang Binh is very abundant and reasonably priced, with distinct cooking methods such as fish hotpot, fish salad, steamed crab, fried ram, fish sauce... Fish salad is usually grouper or apricot fish. The fish is dipped in lemon juice and rolled with rice paper and various kinds of rice paper. Fish salad is widely sold at seafood restaurants in the center of Dong Hoi city and boat restaurants on Nhat Le river.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Potato fish hotpot</b>: also known as fish porridge is also a specialty sold at many restaurants in Dong Hoi City. A rustic hot pot with tomatoes, star fruit, tamarind leaves, sour bamboo shoots, and sauerkraut creates a delicious taste for the soft pieces of fish and potatoes that melt in the mouth. Diners can order seafood with it.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Melaleuca mushrooms</b>: not available everywhere and in every season. This specialty is only available around April and July-August of the lunar calendar, each season lasting about 5-7 days after each rain. Mushrooms grow on Melaleuca trees, have a bitter taste, are used stir-fried with vegetables, pork, shrimp or cooked in soup or porridge.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2 mb-4"><b>Sticky sweet potatoes</b>: made from potatoes that have been soaked in water after harvest and are slightly dry. When the potatoes are less fresh and the surface is no longer plump and bright, wash them, boil them, then peel them and slice them thinly, then dry them in the sun for 7 to 9 days to get soft sweet potatoes. Delicious potato slices have the color of cockroach wings, are flexible and sweet, and have a characteristic potato aroma.</p>
